SCHOEMANSKLOOF &#8211; A truck driver was killed after allegedly swerving to miss other traffic earlier today.ER 24 confirmed that there was only one casualty. The truck went off the side of the road, as it could not brake in time due to its heavy metal load.Netcare 911 was the first on scene, and the fire department is working with jaws of life to cut the vehicle so that authorities can retrieve the body.ER 24 stated that 1100 cars come through the toll gates from Machado Plaza every hour, and due to high volumes of traffic and wet road conditions, the N4 is extremely dangerous and cautions drivers to slow down, as this would be the second fatality for the day on the N4.Also read: BREAKING NEWS: New Zealand Missionary dies in crash